# Component pattern

Every component in Mona Lisa Overdrive follows this exact shape. Do not
deviate without updating this rule first.

## Directory layout

src/components/button/
├── button.tsx        # Implementation
├── button.variants.ts # CVA definitions (if complex)
├── button.stories.tsx # Storybook
├── button.test.tsx   # Vitest
└── index.ts          # Explicit named re-exports

## The canonical shape

```tsx
import { forwardRef } from "react";
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "@/lib/cn";

const buttonVariants = cva(
  // base classes — use semantic tokens via tailwind
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-solid disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
  {
    variants: {
      intent: {
        primary: "bg-accent-solid text-accent-fg hover:bg-accent-emphasis",
        secondary: "bg-bg-subtle text-fg-default hover:bg-bg-muted",
        ghost: "hover:bg-bg-subtle",
      },
      size: {
        sm: "h-8 px-3 text-sm",
        md: "h-10 px-4 text-base",
        lg: "h-12 px-6 text-lg",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: { intent: "primary", size: "md" },
  }
);

export type ButtonProps = React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> &
  VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants>;

export const Button = forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ className, intent, size, ...props }, ref) => (
    <button
      ref={ref}
      data-slot="button"
      className={cn(buttonVariants({ intent, size }), className)}
      {...props}
    />
  )
);
Button.displayName = "Button";
```

## Non-negotiable

- `forwardRef` + `displayName`
- `data-slot` attribute
- CVA for variants (not `if/else`)
- `cn()` helper for className merging
- Props extend the native element's props
- Named export only